                     <author>
                Muhammad 'Ali Khan, 'the Nabob of Arcot', ruler of the Carnatic 
                
                
                
              </author>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc"/>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt"/>
                     <title xml:lang="ar"/>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" type="alt"/>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="desc">Legal persian letter</title>
                     <note> Letter in Persian, shikastah, with authority of Moghul Emperor Shah 'Alam II (1759-1806) from Muhammad 'Ali Khan, 'the Nabob of Arcot', ruler of the Carnatic (AH1162/AD1749-AH1210/AD1795)], referring to Qutb ad-Daulah Bahadur, dated AH1178/AD1764. Large seal impression carries name of emperor and nabob. There are also about thirty lines of a south Indian script. [Possibly connected with Sir J. Murray MacGregor]. This letter refers to an amount gold that they will receive by renting a land for three years. The amount of the gold that they will receive is based on the currency value at Bazar karafieh. </note>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar" type="basmalla"> مه آنکه در مورد احوال شماها</incipit>
